A former BBNaija contestant and actress, Diane Russet, has offered prayers on self-perception. The “Pepper Dem” edition housemate wished people would have self-petception but not through the lenses of others.   Wife to donate kidney to Eedris Abdulkareem     ‘Peter Obi can only win on Twitter’     Mixed reactions over PSquare’s comeback songs   Russet hoped people would not only stop seeing themselves from others point of view but more importantly never through the stand point of those that never believed in them. “May we stop seeing ourselves through the eyes of people that never saw us,” the 26-year-old media personality wrote.